full_text: Was Hong Kong ever famous for peanuts?\n\nI know this sound weird (bear with me) but I’ve been going through a box of old things I collected from childhood, and for some reason I have a large porcelain peanut that I remember getting from a trip to Hong Kong circa 1990.
name: Tracy Alloway

full_text: I have no idea why this was being sold in Hong Kong tourist stores at the time, or why this was the one thing I wanted to buy to commemorate the trip.\n\nAll I can think is it vaguely resembles a Nutter Butter and seven- year-old me was hungry.
name: Tracy Alloway

full_text: I can’t find my Magic the Gathering cards but for some reason I still have a porcelain peanut whose only reason for existence seems to be to give me confusing ideas about the nature of Hong Kong’s historic economy.
name: Tracy Alloway
